\begin{figure}[t]
 \begin{center}
 \includegraphics[width=0.45\linewidth]{pre_bounce_index_gamma.eps}
 \quad
 \includegraphics[width=0.45\linewidth]{pre_bounce_index_q.eps}
 \caption
 {\label{f:indices_pbb}
Here we illustrate the dominant spectral indices $n_u$ (solid) and
$n_v$ (dashed) on super-Hubble scales which are obtained after a
'stable', regular transition of the corresponding variable to the
radiation era at sufficiently late time. This is also the
resulting spectral index for the Bardeen potential on
cosmologically relevant scales. The left panel shows the indices
as a function of $\gamma_{-}$, the exponent of the pump field
during the pre-big bang phase. The right panel shows them as a
function of $q$, the exponent of the contraction (expansion) law
before the big bang. We have used $\gamma_{u_{-}}=-q$ and
$\gamma_{v_{-}}=q$.}
 \end{center}
\

