We illustrate the spectral distribution ${\cal P}_v = |v|^2 k^3$
of case~2 as a function of the rescaled comoving wavenumber
$k/k_{m}$. The parameters for the simulations are $\epsilon =
10^{-2}$, $q=0.3$ and the spectral distribution is evaluated in
the radiation era at $\eta/\eta_s=10^3$. We confront our
predictions for the spectral slopes, above and below the kink at
$k_{v_1}/k_{m}\sim 10^{-8}-10^{-7}$, the decaying mode is still
dominant on scales $k\leqslant k_{v_1}$.}
 \label{f:spectre-v-cases/fit-q=0.3}
